         <abstract>
            <p>It is shown that the Ritz projection onto spaces of piecewise linear finite elements is bounded in the Sobolev space, $\overset{\circ}{W}_p^1$, for $2 \leqslant p \leqslant \infty$. This implies that for functions in $\overset{\circ}{W}_p^1 \cap W_p^2$ the error in approximation behaves like $O(h)$ in $W_p^1$, for $2 \leqslant p \leqslant \infty$, and like $O(h^2)$ in $L_p$, for $2 \leqslant p &lt; \infty$. In all these cases the additional logarithmic factor previously included in error estimates for linear finite elements does not occur.</p>
          </abstract>
